âœ… Clean & Correct Version (Using Math Only):

num = int(input("Enter a number: "))
reversed_num = 0

while num > 0:
    last_digit = num % 10
    reversed_num = reversed_num * 10 + last_digit
    num = num // 10

print("Reversed number:", reversed_num)
âœ… If I Want to Use a List:

num = int(input("Enter a number: "))
list1 = []

while num > 0:
    last_digit = num % 10
    num = num // 10
    list1.append(str(last_digit))  # Convert to string here

result_reverse = ''.join(list1)
print("Reversed number:", result_reverse)
